resources.description:
This endpoint allows you to check the status of the database using NestJS health checks.

**URL:** `GET http://localhost:8000/health-check/db`

### Response
A successful response when the database is up will have a status code of 200 OK and include the database status information in the response body.

```
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "ok",
  "info": {
    "database": {
      "status": "up"
    }
  },
  "error": {},
  "details": {
    "database": {
      "status": "up"
    }
  }
}

```

If the database is down or if there is an issue, the response will have a status code of 503 Service Unavailable and include the error message.

```
HTTP/1.1 503 Service Unavailable
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "database": {
    "status": "down",
    "message": "timeout of 1000ms exceeded"
  }
}

```
